messages.text: That was strange. Where am I?
Something is really messed up with the area around here. Looks like desert haze, but... I can see other places in it?
I'm definitely looking at different time periods through these. Some of these go back thousands of years. I'm calling these "time holes" until I think of a better name.
Hey! I saw another Barry in one of the holes and called out, and he seemed to notice. It looks like I could influence the past, at least with very short messages. Maybe I'll start with "more water."
For now, I could safely get time to pass about 5X as fast. That'll be better than watching radishes grow.
[something about this taking a while]
Hey, there's an old #7291 generator here! I can't believe they still use these. It's not working, but I could fix it if I had the parts.
It's reassembled, but still won't start. Maybe there's a troubleshooting guide around here.
Hours later, I gave up, and finally found it taped to the bottom of the generator. Someone's laughing right now.
It's running! The lights are on. Time to see what else powered up. There isn't much that'll run off this.
Turns out it's like focusing on one of those Magic Eye images - just defocus, and the computer takes over. I bet I can use this technique to shove much more information into Past Barry's head.
Here we go. I found a method of compressing food into smaller containers. That should help out with preservation.
Found a "Mr Fusion" in pretty good condition. Guess I should feed it?
There's a really interesting time hole up some stairs, but I'll have to move some wreckage out of the way to get to it.
I'm exhausted and never want to lift heavy things again, but I can get to the time hole now.
After a lot of arguing with Past Barry, we agreed to jump in and swap places when the time comes. I have no idea what'll happen to him, but that sounds like Future Barry problems, not mine.
Here we go! One unused carbon nanotube filter. This would have been really useful back in the day. With enough power, I should be able to send this back to Past Barry.
Mr. Fusion just coughed up the last of what I gave it and let off some smoke. I think it's generated its last.
There's a promising RIMC coupe left on blocks with decent tires. Windows are smashed, battery's dead, fuel cell's empty. I'm not fixing the windows.
Found a half-full cell in a nearby car, and with a lot of effort, got it installed. I just have to deal with that battery now.
I had to push the car a half-mile, but IT'S ALIVE! This thing is in rough shape, but I hope it'll make it to the next town.
Rough trip, but I'm finally glad I lived near a tech hub. Lots of places to explore here.
There's a whole stockpile of smartphone-looking things, and nearly every battery on every one of these is dead. Maybe one of them is still alive.

Found one! This is way beyond a smartphone - it could purchase just about anything in the world in one tap. Future people were even more into buying stuff than we were. I'll send one of these to Past Barry right away.

Found something - a compact condensate capture system. This can pull water right out of the air instead of waiting for rainfall. Past Barry would have loved this. It's too bad the air's too dry for it to be of any use here.
